/-!
# M√∂bius Decomposition Infrastructure

Infrastructure lemmas for the multiplicative M√∂bius decomposition described in ¬ß3.2
of the Granville‚ÄìKurlberg paper. These support the eventual proof of
`deviation_sum_bound_q_indep` in `CancellationHelpers.lean`.

## Main Results

* `PoissonCRT.crt_counting_mobius_decomp`: The M√∂bius inversion sum over
  `n.divisorsAntidiagonal` splits into a **main term** `Œº(n) ¬∑ f(1)` (from the pair
  `(n, 1)`) and an **error sum** `‚àë_{d|n, d>1} Œº(n/d) ¬∑ f(d)` over proper divisors.
  This is the algebraic identity that reorganises the counting function into the
  form `‚àë_{d|q, d>1}`.

* `PoissonCRT.d_contribution_bound`: When a function `f` sums to zero over all
  residue classes (as guaranteed by `deviation_sum_period_zero`) and is pointwise
  bounded by `M` (as guaranteed by `individual_deviation_bound`), the weighted
  sum `‚àë w ¬∑ f` is controlled by the **total variation** of the weights from any
  constant `c` times `M`. The total variation captures exactly the boundary
  (incomplete-period) contribution for a single divisor `d`, and is bounded by
  `box_card_upper_bound` applied with scaling `s/d`.

* `PoissonCRT.divisor_sum_convergence`: The p-series `‚àë d^{-(k-2+Œµ)}` converges
  whenever the exponent exceeds 1. For `k ‚â• 3` this is automatic; for `k = 2`
  the critical exponent `Œª‚ÇÇ` ensures convergence via a separate bound.

## References

* [A. Granville, P. Kurlberg, *Poisson statistics via the Chinese remainder theorem*],
  ¬ß3.2
-/

